<TITLE> Bus kills 5 schoolgoers in Chittagong </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, August 13 (bdnews24.com)  A bus ran over an autorickshaw Monday morning on Chittagong-Dhaka highway at Sitakunda, killing seven people, five of them school students, police said. Sitakunda police chief Abdus Salam told bdnews24.com a Hanif Enterprise passenger coach ran over the CNG-run autorickshaw coming from the opposite direction at around 7:30 am at Chhoto Kumira roundabout, leaving six dead on the spot. Another died from wounds after the injured were taken to the Chittagong Medical College Hospital (CMCH), he said. None of the deceased could be immediately identified. The police chief and eye-witnesses said the impact of the speeding coach killed all the five autorickshaw passengers and a passerby instantly. Agitated bystanders barricaded the highway immediately after the incident and torched the bus, leading to a huge traffic held-up. The local law enforcers cleared the highway at 10:30am. Sub-inspector Zahir of CMCH police post said four injured during the accident were admitted to the hospital, of whom one died subsequently. The three receiving treatment at the CMCH were Mohammad Noman, 13, Irfan, 12 and Kamal Hossain, 10, he said. bdnews
